President Trump announces that the United States, along with Mexico and Canada, will be hosting the World Cup in 2026. He thanks Gianni Infantino, the president of FIFA, for his role in making this happen. Trump also praises Carlos Cordeiro, the president of the U.S. Soccer Federation, for his efforts in securing the World Cup bid. The president expresses his excitement for the event and discusses the growth of soccer as a sport. He also mentions his son's love for soccer and his hopes for organizing the greatest World Cup ever. The conversation shifts to the topic of Google and other tech companies, with Trump expressing concerns about their practices and suggesting that they may be taking advantage of people. He warns that these companies need to be careful as they are treading on troubled territory and potentially being unfair to large portions of the population.